	<div id="p4861" class="post bg2">
		<div class="inner">

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p4861"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=4861#p4861"><img src="./styles/modestus/imageset/icon_post_target.png" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=377">lyosha</a></strong> &raquo; Thu Mar 12, 2009 7:52 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">Make it something like this and we'll be happy:
<br />
<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>&lt;style&gt;<br />h1 &#123;background-image: url&#40;'chocolate.png'&#41; no-repeat;&#125;<br />h1 span &#123;display: none;&#125;<br />&lt;/style&gt;<br /><br />&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;The chocolate headline&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />I personally am not a fan of images as headings, but this is a real life thing and is somewhat acceptable.<br /><br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div>Extreme example, but you get what I am trying to point out, right? Why not something like this?<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>&lt;p src=&quot;ode.png&quot;&gt;How wonderful is chocolate?&lt;br /&gt;How can I express my delight?&lt;/p&gt;</code></dd></dl> or even <dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>&lt;img src=&quot;chocolate.png&quot;&gt;I &lt;strong&gt;love&lt;/strong&gt; chocolate!&lt;/img&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />I'm sure it's been discussed before, but anyone want to help elaborate why this wouldn't work?</div></blockquote>
<br />
<br />Completely not backwards compatible which is HTML 5's goal. (although there is the &lt;legend&gt; mess which isn't backwards compatible.)</div>

			

		</div>

		
